k: RISC-V SoC Optimization — SPM, DMA, GEMV Parallelization, Inline ASM

## Context

This is an AS501 Final Project — a RISC-V (RV32I+M) CPU running LSTM Seq2Seq inference (German→English translation) on TSMC 28nm. The RTL is in SystemVerilog.

Currently the design has: Scalar Core (RV32IM with HW multiplier), Instruction Cache, MCU (memory controller), GEMV accelerator (sequential MAC, very slow), Data Cache (2KB direct-mapped, GEMV-only), and a simple priority-MUX arbiter. **There is no SPM and no DMA.** All data accesses go to external DMEM with 40ns (4-cycle) latency every time.

The current GEMV accelerator processes one MAC per cycle (sequential), which provides almost no speedup over the CPU doing the same GEMV with hardware `mul`/`mulh` instructions. It needs to be parallelized with multiple PEs.

