1. **Part 0** first (SW check — quick, no RTL changes)
2. **Part 1** (SPM — standalone module, no dependencies)
3. **Part 2** (DMA — standalone module, no dependencies)
4. **Part 3** (MCU modification — needs to know SPM/DMA interfaces from Parts 1-2)
5. **Part 4** (cpu_top wiring + arbiter update — integrates everything)
6. **Part 5** (GEMV parallelization — independent of SPM/DMA, can be done anytime)
7. **Part 6** (Testbench — final integration check)

