## Coding Style
- Use SystemVerilog (`.sv`)
- Follow existing code conventions (see `mcu.sv` and `gemv_accel.sv` for style reference)
- Use `always_ff` for sequential, `always_comb` for combinational
- Use `logic` not `reg`/`wire`
- Active-low reset (`rst_ni`)
- Include `ifdef SIM` / `else` blocks for SRAM: behavioral array for sim, TSMC macro for synthesis
- All new modules must have a copyright header matching the existing style
